{
  "text": "This section of the paper will rely on the fact that any finite type subsurface of a genus zero surface has mapping class group isomorphic to the braid group. [CITATION_1] contains some results and discussion on infinite stranded braid groups and its connections to the mapping class group of a disk with infinitely many punctures.",
  "citation_candidates": [
